{"info": {"author": "Karel Vesely", "author_email": "", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Multimedia :: Sound/Audio :: Speech"], "description": "kaldi-io-for-python\n===================\n'Glue' code connecting kaldi data and python.\n-----------------------------------------------\n\n#### Supported data types\n- vector (integer)\n- Vector (float, double)\n- Matrix (float, double)\n- Posterior (posteriors, nnet1 training targets, confusion networks, ...)\n\n#### Examples\n\n###### Reading feature scp example:\n\n```python\nimport kaldi_io\nfor key,mat in kaldi_io.read_mat_scp(file):\n  ...\n```\n\n###### Writing feature ark to file/stream:\n```python\nimport kaldi_io\nwith open(ark_file,'wb') as f:\n  for key,mat in dict.iteritems():\n    kaldi_io.write_mat(f, mat, key=key)\n```\n\n###### Writing features as 'ark,scp' by pipeline with 'copy-feats':\n```python\nimport kaldi_io\nark_scp_output='ark:| copy-feats --compress=true ark:- ark,scp:data/feats2.ark,data/feats2.scp'\nwith kaldi_io.open_or_fd(ark_scp_output,'wb') as f:\n  for key,mat in dict.iteritems():\n    kaldi_io.write_mat(f, mat, key=key)\n```\n\n#### Install\n- from pypi: `python -m pip --user install kaldi_io`\n- from sources:\n  - `git clone https://github.com/vesis84/kaldi-io-for-python.git <kaldi-io-dir>`\n  - `python setup.py install` (default python)\n- for local development use: `export PYTHONPATH=${PYTHONPATH}:<kaldi-io-dir>` in `$HOME/.bashrc`\n\nNote: it is recommended to set `$KALDI_ROOT` in your `$HOME/.bashrc` as\n`export KALDI_ROOT=<some_kaldi_dir>`, so you can read/write using\npipes which contain kaldi binaries.\n\n\n#### License\nApache License, Version 2.0 ('LICENSE-2.0.txt')\n\n#### Contact\n- If you have an extension to share, please create a pull request.\n- For feedback and suggestions, please create a GitHub 'Issue' in the project.\n- For the positive reactions =) I am also reachable by email: vesis84@gmail.com\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/vesis84/kaldi-io-for-python", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "kaldi-io", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/kaldi-io/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/kaldi-io/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/vesis84/kaldi-io-for-python"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/kaldi-io/0.9.4/", "requires_dist": ["numpy (>=1.15.3)"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "Glue code connecting Kaldi data and Python.", "version": "0.9.4", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>kaldi-io-for-python</h1>\n<h2>'Glue' code connecting kaldi data and python.</h2>\n<h4>Supported data types</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>vector (integer)</li>\n<li>Vector (float, double)</li>\n<li>Matrix (float, double)</li>\n<li>Posterior (posteriors, nnet1 training targets, confusion networks, ...)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Examples</h4>\n<h6>Reading feature scp example:</h6>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">kaldi_io</span>\n<span class=\"k\">for</span> <span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"n\">mat</span> <span class=\"ow\">in</span> <span class=\"n\">kaldi_io</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">read_mat_scp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">...</span>\n</pre>\n<h6>Writing feature ark to file/stream:</h6>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">kaldi_io</span>\n<span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"nb\">open</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ark_file</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"s1\">'wb'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"k\">for</span> <span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"n\">mat</span> <span class=\"ow\">in</span> <span class=\"nb\">dict</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">iteritems</span><span class=\"p\">():</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">kaldi_io</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">write_mat</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">mat</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<h6>Writing features as 'ark,scp' by pipeline with 'copy-feats':</h6>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">kaldi_io</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ark_scp_output</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s1\">'ark:| copy-feats --compress=true ark:- ark,scp:data/feats2.ark,data/feats2.scp'</span>\n<span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"n\">kaldi_io</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">open_or_fd</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ark_scp_output</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"s1\">'wb'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"k\">for</span> <span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"n\">mat</span> <span class=\"ow\">in</span> <span class=\"nb\">dict</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">iteritems</span><span class=\"p\">():</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">kaldi_io</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">write_mat</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">mat</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<h4>Install</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>from pypi: <code>python -m pip --user install kaldi_io</code></li>\n<li>from sources:\n<ul>\n<li><code>git clone https://github.com/vesis84/kaldi-io-for-python.git &lt;kaldi-io-dir&gt;</code></li>\n<li><code>python setup.py install</code> (default python)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>for local development use: <code>export PYTHONPATH=${PYTHONPATH}:&lt;kaldi-io-dir&gt;</code> in <code>$HOME/.bashrc</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Note: it is recommended to set <code>$KALDI_ROOT</code> in your <code>$HOME/.bashrc</code> as\n<code>export KALDI_ROOT=&lt;some_kaldi_dir&gt;</code>, so you can read/write using\npipes which contain kaldi binaries.</p>\n<h4>License</h4>\n<p>Apache License, Version 2.0 ('LICENSE-2.0.txt')</p>\n<h4>Contact</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>If you have an extension to share, please create a pull request.</li>\n<li>For feedback and suggestions, please create a GitHub 'Issue' in the project.</li>\n<li>For the positive reactions =) I am also reachable by email: <a href=\"mailto:vesis84@gmail.com\">vesis84@gmail.com</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6938050, "releases": {"0.9.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "380dad12533293fb691c953cc9a0b48f", "sha256": "55cae1a5c4d89c522cbb6798f1ca93b9edf336a8960f784ca31518c57b85e047"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "kaldi_io-0.9.0-py2-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "380dad12533293fb691c953cc9a0b48f", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py2", "requires_python": null, "size": 10164, "upload_time": "2019-02-12T14:29:23", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-02-12T14:29:23.773643Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/dc/2f/fe96915dd5653e5b5032eea6211e3f1bbe87bca84f5fce592e95ca7cba5c/kaldi_io-0.9.0-py2-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "a6814c2595f94113147d34c43fe7b23f", "sha256": "2223e4fcdea1154dd13ebca4bb97bbcdad91495af5e94a0045ff9a41498098c6"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "kaldi_io-0.9.0-py3-none-any.whl